wikipedia_page.main: James "Jim" Crossley (birth unknown – death unknown) was an English professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1930s and 1940s. He played at club level for Castleford (Heritage № 136), as a second-row, i.e. number 11 or 12, during the era of contested scrums.
